pollutant_name: Ultra Fine Particles (UFPs) -  recommended unit: particles.cm-3
definition: Ultra Fine Particles (UFPs) means particles with a diameter less than or equal to 100 nanometers (10^-9 m), where UFP are measured as the particle number concentrations per cubic centimetre for a size range with a lower limit of 10 nm and for a size range with no restriction on the upper limit

particle number size distribution (PNSD) is the frequency distribution of the particle number concentration represented as a function of the logarithm of particle size, such that the area under the distribution between two sizes is the number concentration of that size range.
